WEBVTT

01:45.959 --> 01:48.125
PREVIOUSLY ON "DEXTER"...

01:48.125 --> 01:51.542
Dexter: NO BLOOD --
WHAT A BEAUTIFUL IDEA.

01:51.542 --> 01:55.375
Debra: Brother, I just found
the fucking ice truck.

01:59.750 --> 02:01.959
IT IS MY NEW FRIEND.

02:01.959 --> 02:04.208
WHEN HE BROKE INTO
MY APARTMENT,

02:04.208 --> 02:06.792
HE TOOK SOME TIME
TO GET TO KNOW ME --

02:06.792 --> 02:10.417
MY LIFE, MY SECRETS.

02:10.417 --> 02:12.417
PAUL DOESN'T
LIVE HERE ANYMORE.

02:12.417 --> 02:15.041
[ LAUGHS ] NO SHIT.
HE'S IN JAIL.

02:15.041 --> 02:18.667
BUT, SEE, HE STILL OWES ME
FOR TWO OUNCES OF BLOW,

02:18.667 --> 02:20.333
WHICH MEANS YOU OWE ME.

02:20.333 --> 02:22.333
THE COYOTE WANTED MORE MONEY,
AND I DIDN'T HAVE IT.

02:22.333 --> 02:25.083
POOR BASTARDS --
SPEND THEIR LIFE SAVINGS,

02:25.083 --> 02:26.458
GET STUFFED INTO A FISHHOLD.

02:26.458 --> 02:27.709
IF THEY CAN'T PAY...

02:27.709 --> 02:29.375
THEY DISAPPEAR.

02:29.375 --> 02:31.041
JORGE CASTILLO --

02:31.041 --> 02:33.542
THE ONLY SUSPECT EVEN
REMOTELY CLOSE TO THE PARK

02:33.542 --> 02:35.917
WHERE YELINA WAS SUPPOSED TO
DROP THE MONEY.

02:35.917 --> 02:38.000
EXCUSE ME.
PRIVATE YARD.

02:39.166 --> 02:41.417
SORRY, I JUST ASSUMED
YOU WERE CUBAN.

02:42.750 --> 02:45.125
AMERICAN, PAL,
JUST LIKE YOU.

02:49.083 --> 02:50.625
JUST LIKE ME.

02:50.625 --> 02:53.041
COÑO.

02:53.041 --> 02:55.709
GET BACK IN THERE,
YOU CUBAN PIECE OF SHIT.

02:55.709 --> 02:57.542
THEY'RE EVEN BETTER-MATCHED
THAN I THOUGHT.

02:59.291 --> 03:00.792
FUCKING ANIMALS.

03:00.792 --> 03:03.542
God bless America.

03:03.542 --> 03:05.125
NO.

03:05.125 --> 03:06.542
[ GROANING ]

03:07.792 --> 03:09.458
[ MUFFLED SCREAMS ]

03:09.458 --> 03:12.041
TAKING THE EXTRA TIME
TO KILL VALERIE

03:12.041 --> 03:13.417
MAY HAVE BEEN ILL-ADVISED.

03:13.417 --> 03:15.000
MY LIFE HAS ALWAYS BEEN
A SEQUENCE

03:15.000 --> 03:18.125
OF CAREFULLY PLANNED MOMENTS.

03:18.125 --> 03:21.041
BUT SOMETIMES
YOU JUST HAVE TO TAKE A RISK.

03:36.834 --> 03:41.000
LIFE IS SO FLEETING,
SO FRAGILE,

03:41.000 --> 03:44.000
EVERY BREATH THE POTENTIAL
TO BE OUR LAST.

03:46.792 --> 03:48.208
YOU READY?

03:58.250 --> 04:00.291
CAN I HAVE
MY CEREAL NOW?

04:00.291 --> 04:02.333
WE ALL GRIEVE IN OUR OWN WAY.

04:02.333 --> 04:03.333
SURE.

04:04.333 --> 04:07.583
I PREFER
THE 6-YEAR-OLD APPROACH.

04:07.583 --> 04:10.875
YET ANOTHER I'VE SENT
TO A WATERY GRAVE.

04:10.875 --> 04:13.375
WELL, NOT QUITE.

04:21.041 --> 04:22.959
HEY,
WHAT ABOUT THIS ONE?

04:22.959 --> 04:24.542
I WANT ANGEL CAKE.

04:24.542 --> 04:27.709
IT'S ANGEL FOOD, STUPID,
AND YOU DON'T GET A VOTE.

04:27.709 --> 04:28.709
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY.

04:28.709 --> 04:29.792
GUYS.

04:33.375 --> 04:36.000
SO HOW'D IT GO?

04:36.000 --> 04:39.500
BOB THE GOLDFISH --
MAY HE REST IN PEACE.

04:39.500 --> 04:40.834
THANKS FOR COMING OVER

04:40.834 --> 04:42.667
AND TAKING CARE OF THIS
FOR ME.

04:42.667 --> 04:43.792
DEAD STUFF.

04:43.792 --> 04:45.625
I KNOW.

04:45.625 --> 04:48.208
WELL, GO HAVE A SEAT.

04:48.208 --> 04:50.750
YOUR TREAT FOR COMING OVER EARLY
IS ON ITS WAY.

04:52.500 --> 04:54.417
[ IMITATES DOG BARKING ]

04:54.417 --> 04:58.625
I DON'T GET BIRTHDAYS --
THE PARTY, A SONG.

04:58.625 --> 05:04.250
CELEBRATING ANOTHER YEAR
JUST BEING ALIVE FEELS FORCED.

05:04.250 --> 05:06.834
THAT ONE.
THAT'S THE ONE I WANT.

05:06.834 --> 05:08.750
Rita: COCONUT IT IS.

05:08.750 --> 05:11.166
I HATE COCONUT.

05:11.166 --> 05:13.041
YOU'VE NEVER HAD COCONUT.

05:13.041 --> 05:15.709
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

05:15.709 --> 05:17.208
Dexter: IT'S DISPATCH.

05:17.208 --> 05:19.083
I MIGHT HAVE TO SETTLE
FOR TOAST TO GO.

05:19.083 --> 05:20.458
MORGAN.

05:23.291 --> 05:25.458
SURE, WHAT'S THE LOCATION?

05:29.417 --> 05:31.166
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

05:40.917 --> 05:42.625
THE CRIME SCENE.

05:44.000 --> 05:45.333
MY CRIME SCENE.

05:47.834 --> 05:49.125
[ CRYING ]

06:04.000 --> 06:06.375
[ MUFFLED SCREAMS ]

06:06.375 --> 06:08.333
I SHOULDN'T HAVE
KILLED THEM BOTH.

06:08.333 --> 06:10.500
I DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH TIME.

06:10.500 --> 06:15.041
A FOOTPRINT,
A MICROSCOPIC DROP OF BLOOD --

06:15.041 --> 06:17.166
WHAT DID I LEAVE BEHIND?

06:35.083 --> 06:37.542
IMPOSSIBLE.

06:39.166 --> 06:41.041
NICE PLACE SETTING,
HUH?

06:41.041 --> 06:42.583
WE'RE RUNNING
HER PRINTS NOW.

06:42.583 --> 06:45.500
IT HAD TO BE HIM.
HE'S WATCHING ME.

06:45.500 --> 06:47.166
DEX?

06:48.375 --> 06:50.333
GOOD.

06:50.333 --> 06:52.333
I.D. THE VICTIM.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.041
YOU FIND ANYTHING ELSE?

07:00.041 --> 07:01.500
THAT AIN'T ENOUGH?

07:01.500 --> 07:02.917
ANY EYEWITNESSES?

07:02.917 --> 07:04.834
JUST DO YOUR JOB.
WORRY ABOUT THE BLOOD.

07:04.834 --> 07:07.625
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

07:07.625 --> 07:09.375
YOU GONNA ANSWER THAT?

07:13.291 --> 07:14.875
THIS TIN CAN
SMELLS LIKE ASS.

07:14.875 --> 07:16.291
THE SOONER YOU GET BUSY,

07:16.291 --> 07:19.792
THE SOONER WE CAN FINGER
WHO DID THIS.

07:19.792 --> 07:21.458
YOU HEARD THE MAN.

07:33.709 --> 07:38.333
HE DOVE 100 FEET
TO BRING UP THE BODY.

07:38.333 --> 07:39.792
HE'S GETTING BACK AT ME

07:39.792 --> 07:41.917
FOR NOT KILLING
THAT SECURITY GUARD.

07:43.625 --> 07:45.667
PLEASE TELL ME THIS WASN'T
THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER.

07:45.667 --> 07:47.333
I'VE GOT THE PRESS
SNIFFING OUTSIDE.

07:47.333 --> 07:48.709
NO, IT'S NOT HIS M.O.

07:48.709 --> 07:50.583
WE GOT AN I.D. --
VALERIE CASTILLO.

07:50.583 --> 07:52.500
HER HUSBAND, JORGE,
OWNS THE SALVAGE YARD.

07:52.500 --> 07:54.583
WELL, THEN,
TRY AND TRACK HIM DOWN.

07:54.583 --> 07:57.625
Man:
Sir, we found something.

08:02.959 --> 08:04.417
YOU GOT ANYTHING?

08:04.417 --> 08:08.417
Masuka: NO BRUISING.
NOTHING UNDER HER NAILS.

08:08.417 --> 08:11.125
SHE DIDN'T PUT UP A FIGHT.

08:11.125 --> 08:13.250
IF SHE WAS KILLED HERE,
WHICH I DOUBT,

08:13.250 --> 08:15.583
WHOEVER DID IT
WAS A REAL PRO.

08:15.583 --> 08:18.750
UNDER NORMAL CIRCUMSTANCES,
I'D TAKE THAT AS A COMPLIMENT.

08:18.750 --> 08:19.583
PRINTS?

08:19.583 --> 08:21.458
SHE'S CLEAN.

08:21.458 --> 08:24.667
THIS TRAILER --
THAT'S ANOTHER MATTER.

08:24.667 --> 08:28.458
I DON'T EVEN WANT TO KNOW
WHAT SOME OF THOSE STAINS ARE.

08:30.250 --> 08:32.625
YO, DEX,
I THINK I FOUND SOMETHING.

08:32.625 --> 08:34.375
ZOOM IN ON THIS,
WILL YOU?

08:34.375 --> 08:36.458
I'M KIND OF LOW
ON BATTERIES HERE.

08:36.458 --> 08:38.667
DUDE, IT'LL TAKE, LIKE,
TWO SECONDS.

08:40.709 --> 08:43.417
YO, WHAT'S UP WITH YOU TODAY?
YOU'RE THROWING OFF MY CHI.

08:43.417 --> 08:44.959
YOU'RE NOT CHINESE.

08:44.959 --> 08:46.000
I'M NOT?

08:46.000 --> 08:47.792
LOOK, RIGHT HERE.

08:49.458 --> 08:52.542
DOES THAT LOOK LIKE
A NEEDLE MARK TO YOU?

08:54.250 --> 08:57.542
IT'S MORE LIKE A BUG BITE,
BLEMISH MAYBE.

09:00.083 --> 09:03.500
YEAH, I GUESS.

09:05.500 --> 09:08.458
I'M GONNA LET
THE CORONER BAG HER.

09:08.458 --> 09:10.250
I'M HUNGRY.

09:15.041 --> 09:16.709
[ SIGHS ]

09:20.000 --> 09:22.834
OH...

09:22.834 --> 09:24.834
THIS AIN'T NO AUTO GARAGE.

09:24.834 --> 09:26.834
OH!

09:26.834 --> 09:27.834
OH, GOD.

09:27.834 --> 09:29.667
OH, I DIDN'T NEED
TO SEE THAT.

09:29.667 --> 09:32.000
YOU NEVER SEEN
A LATRINE BEFORE, MORGAN?

09:32.000 --> 09:34.667
YEAH, JUST NOT INDOORS.

09:34.667 --> 09:36.500
WELL, THE ARMY TAUGHT ME
A LOT OF THINGS.

09:36.500 --> 09:38.750
I FEEL A DESERT STORM STORY
COMING ON.

09:38.750 --> 09:40.625
DIGGING HOLES FOR PEOPLE
TO TAKE A DUMP?

09:40.625 --> 09:42.709
THAT WAS MOST IMPORTANT.

09:42.709 --> 09:44.709
I'M NOT REALLY GETTING THAT.

09:44.709 --> 09:46.875
IT DOESN'T MATTER HOW MANY BARS
YOU GOT ON YOUR COLLAR.

09:46.875 --> 09:50.208
EVERYBODY'S SHIT STINKS.
WE WERE PARTNERS A LONG TIME.

09:50.208 --> 09:51.625
FROM THE LOOKS OF THINGS,

09:51.625 --> 09:54.041
VALERIE CASTILLO'S
BETTER HALF WAS KNEE-DEEP.

09:54.041 --> 09:55.667
YOU LIKE THE HUSBAND
FOR THIS?

09:55.667 --> 09:57.625
IT'S ALWAYS THE HUSBAND.

09:59.709 --> 10:02.125
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

10:02.125 --> 10:05.083
IT LOOKS LIKE A PHONE NUMBER
AND A NAME -- MARIEL.

10:05.083 --> 10:07.375
CALL IT IN TO BATISTA.
HE CAN RUN IT DOWN FOR US.

10:07.375 --> 10:09.375
SERGEANT DOAKES.

10:09.375 --> 10:12.208
WE HEARD MOVEMENT
IN THE TRUNK.

10:12.208 --> 10:13.875
I GOT IT.
I GOT IT.

10:18.125 --> 10:20.041
PADRE NUESTRO QUE ESTá
EN LOS CIELOS.

10:20.041 --> 10:22.125
SANTIFICADO SEA TU NOMBRE.
VENGA TU REINO.

10:22.125 --> 10:23.750
HáGASE TU VOLUNTAD
EN LA TIERRA...

10:23.750 --> 10:24.875
YOU ALL RIGHT, KID?

10:24.875 --> 10:26.291
COME ON, MAN.

10:26.291 --> 10:27.583
NO.

10:27.583 --> 10:31.417
SUBTLE.
MAYBE YOU SHOULD CUFF HIM.

10:31.417 --> 10:33.667
MI HIJITO,
TODO ESTá BIEN.

10:33.667 --> 10:35.291
TE VAMOS A AYUDAR.

10:57.041 --> 10:59.417
Dexter:
THE NOOSE IS TIGHTENING.

11:02.041 --> 11:05.125
THIS IS HOW IT ENDS --
IN THE HANDS OF A 7-YEAR-OLD?

11:05.125 --> 11:06.375
HEY, DEB.

11:06.375 --> 11:08.250
I USUALLY LIKE KIDS.

11:08.250 --> 11:09.834
WHO'S THE BOY?

11:09.834 --> 11:11.625
ALL WE GOT SO FAR
IS THAT HE'S CUBAN

11:11.625 --> 11:13.667
AND HE SEEMS TO LIKE
LaGUERTA.

11:13.667 --> 11:16.041
SPEND ENOUGH TIME IN A TRUNK,
SHE'D LOOK GOOD TO ANYBODY.

11:16.041 --> 11:18.375
[ LAUGHS ]

11:18.375 --> 11:21.458
DID HE, YOU KNOW,
SEE ANYTHING?

11:21.458 --> 11:23.458
I'M NOT SURE.
HE'S PRETTY OUT OF IT.

11:23.458 --> 11:25.834
SOCIAL SERVICES
IS ON THE WAY.

11:27.291 --> 11:30.291
YOU OKAY? YOU GOT A WHOLE
BROW THING GOING ON.

11:30.291 --> 11:32.500
MORGAN,
BRING SOME WATER!

11:32.500 --> 11:35.375
[ SIGHS ] I LOVE HER.

11:35.375 --> 11:38.959
MAYBE I SHOULD SPEND SOME TIME
IN A HOT TRUNK, TOO.

11:38.959 --> 11:42.750
MY NEAT LITTLE WORLD OF LIES
IS CRUMBLING ALL AROUND ME,

11:42.750 --> 11:47.208
AND I CAN'T TELL A SOUL,
ESPECIALLY NOT DEB.

11:48.500 --> 11:51.333
DEB,
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

11:51.333 --> 11:52.709
BUT I HAVE MY BOOKS.

11:52.709 --> 11:54.917
I MEAN,
I COULD JUST STAY IN THE CAR

11:54.917 --> 11:56.834
OR I CAN WALK
WITH YOU GUYS.

11:56.834 --> 11:59.417
I PROMISE I'LL BE QUIET.
YOU WON'T EVEN KNOW I'M THERE.

11:59.417 --> 12:01.041
THE PHEASANTS WILL KNOW
YOU'RE THERE.

12:01.041 --> 12:02.375
BUT DEXTER WAS MY AGE
WHEN --

12:02.375 --> 12:04.000
DEB, THAT'S ENOUGH.

12:04.000 --> 12:06.458
THE LOGANS ARE WAITING.
DID YOU PACK YOUR SWIMSUIT?

12:06.458 --> 12:09.208
YES.

12:09.208 --> 12:10.542
GOOD GIRL.

12:10.542 --> 12:12.959
I WANT TO SEE THAT BACKFLIP
WHEN WE COME HOME.

12:12.959 --> 12:14.417
ALL RIGHT.
GO ON OUT TO THE CAR.

12:14.417 --> 12:17.417
WE'LL BE THERE IN A SEC.

12:20.083 --> 12:22.041
SHE DOES KIND OF
HAVE A POINT, DAD.

12:22.041 --> 12:25.250
WHAT WE DO YOUR SISTER
CAN NEVER KNOW ABOUT.

12:25.250 --> 12:28.542
KEEPING THE TRUTH FROM
THE PEOPLE CLOSEST TO YOU

12:28.542 --> 12:31.291
IS HOW YOU'LL SURVIVE...

12:31.291 --> 12:34.041
AND HOW YOU'LL PROTECT THEM
IF ANYTHING EVER GOES WRONG.

12:44.208 --> 12:45.709
GUYS, HURRY UP.

12:45.709 --> 12:48.208
YOU'RE GONNA BE LATE
FOR SCHOOL.

12:48.208 --> 12:49.542
I'M HEADED TO THE STORE.

12:49.542 --> 12:51.041
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
YOU WANT?

12:51.041 --> 12:52.625
BALLOONS AREN'T MUCH
OF A LIST.

12:52.625 --> 12:54.208
IT'S OKAY.

12:54.208 --> 12:55.792
IT DON'T NEED
THAT OTHER STUFF.

12:55.792 --> 12:57.750
IT'S TOO EXPENSIVE.

12:57.750 --> 13:00.834
HOW ABOUT YOU LET ME WORRY
ABOUT THAT STUFF, OKAY?

13:00.834 --> 13:03.417
IT'S YOUR PARTY.
YOU CAN HAVE WHATEVER YOU WANT.

13:03.417 --> 13:05.625
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

13:05.625 --> 13:07.792
[ SIGHS ]

13:09.542 --> 13:11.625
HELLO?

13:11.625 --> 13:12.917
Paul:
Hey, babe, it's me.

13:12.917 --> 13:15.250
GO WAIT IN THE CAR.

13:17.500 --> 13:19.333
WHAT'S WRONG WITH MOM?

13:19.333 --> 13:22.959
SHE ONLY GETS THAT WAY
WHEN SHE'S TALKING TO DAD.

13:25.834 --> 13:27.375
HI.

13:27.375 --> 13:29.834
I WAS ABLE TO TRACK DOWN
THAT NAME, MARIEL,

13:29.834 --> 13:31.625
WITH THE NUMBER
THAT YOU CALLED IN.

13:31.625 --> 13:33.917
SHE'S A CUBAN REFUGEE.
SHE'S STAYING WITH COUSINS.

13:33.917 --> 13:35.458
I HAD A COP BRING HER IN.

13:35.458 --> 13:37.041
WHY SCRATCH THE NUMBER
IN THE FLOOR?

13:37.041 --> 13:38.291
NEXT OF KIN,

13:38.291 --> 13:40.166
IN CASE SOMETHING
HAPPENED TO HER.

13:40.166 --> 13:41.834
GUYS LIKE CASTILLO
ARE RUTHLESS.

13:41.834 --> 13:43.542
THEY PREY ON FAMILIES.

13:43.542 --> 13:45.417
HE WAS HOLDING MARIEL
AND SIX OTHERS CAPTIVE

13:45.417 --> 13:46.667
AT A SALVAGE YARD.

13:46.667 --> 13:48.250
THAT EXPLAINS THE GARAGE.

13:48.250 --> 13:50.291
IF THE RELATIVES
DON'T PAY THE RELEASE FEE,

13:50.291 --> 13:52.542
THE COYOTE WOULD DUMP
THEIR ASS OVERBOARD.

13:52.542 --> 13:54.834
COCKSUCKERS MAKE ME SICK.
COME ON.

13:58.792 --> 14:01.792
MARIEL, ESTOS SON MIS AMIGOS
QUE YO TE DIJE.

14:01.792 --> 14:04.667
SARGENTO DOAKES
Y LA DETECTIVE MORGAN.

14:04.667 --> 14:07.375
PUEDE SENTAR.

14:07.375 --> 14:10.250
MARIEL, WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW JORGE CASTILLO?

14:10.250 --> 14:14.333
¿CUáNDO FUE LA ULTIMA VEZ
QUE Tú VISTE A JORGE CASTILLO?

14:14.333 --> 14:17.458
CUANDO ME ENCERRó CON LOS OTROS
DESPUéS DE BAJARNOS DEL BARCO.

14:17.458 --> 14:19.667
WHEN HE LOCKED HER
AND THE OTHER REFUGEES UP

14:19.667 --> 14:21.625
AFTER PULLING THEM
FROM THE BOAT.

14:21.625 --> 14:25.125
NO TENíAMOS COMIDA NI AGUA.

14:25.125 --> 14:28.291
UN HOMBRE TRATó DE ESCAPAR.
JORGE LO AGARRó Y LO GOLPEó.

14:28.291 --> 14:30.875
THEY WENT WITHOUT FOOD
AND WATER.

14:30.875 --> 14:34.000
SOME GUY TRIED TO ESCAPE,
BUT HE WAS BEATEN BY JORGE.

14:34.000 --> 14:35.458
HOW'D SHE GET FREE?

14:35.458 --> 14:36.792
¿CóMO ESCAPó?

14:36.792 --> 14:39.500
ALGUIEN ABRIó LA PUERTA
AL GARAJE.

14:39.500 --> 14:41.041
Y NOS ESCAPAMOS.

14:41.041 --> 14:44.041
SOMEBODY OPENED THE DOOR
TO THE GARAGE.

14:49.166 --> 14:53.250
CUANDO LOS AGARREN, ESPERO QUE
LOS HAGAN SUFRIR MUCHO,

14:53.250 --> 14:55.834
ESPECIALMENTE ESA CONCHA
QUE NOS TRATó COMO PERRO.

14:55.834 --> 14:59.291
SHE SAID,
"WHEN WE FIND THEM,

14:59.291 --> 15:02.750
"TO MAKE THEM SUFFER
FOR WHAT THEY DID,

15:02.750 --> 15:05.250
ESPECIALLY THAT CONCHA
THAT TREATED HER LIKE A DOG."

15:05.250 --> 15:06.417
CONCHA?

15:06.417 --> 15:07.750
AH, GOT YOU.

15:07.750 --> 15:09.750
FUCK ME.
THE WIFE WAS IN ON IT.

15:09.750 --> 15:12.208
ASK IF SHE KNOWS THE LITTLE BOY
SOCIAL SERVICES PICKED UP.

15:12.208 --> 15:15.458
¿Y QUIéN ERA EL NIÑO PEQUEÑO
QUE ESTABA CON USTED?

15:15.458 --> 15:16.625
¿QUé NIÑO?

15:16.625 --> 15:18.375
YO NUNCA VI UN NIÑO.

15:19.792 --> 15:21.875
SHE NEVER SAW A BOY.

15:26.041 --> 15:29.375
NO HAIR, NO FIBERS,
C.O.D. EXSANGUINATION --

15:29.375 --> 15:30.834
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

15:30.834 --> 15:31.875
YOU'RE HOVERING.

15:31.875 --> 15:34.875
KEEP READING.
WAIT FOR IT.

15:34.875 --> 15:36.375
THIS IS A PRELIM.
I DON'T HAVE TIME --

15:36.375 --> 15:38.208
"M" FUCKING 99.

15:40.291 --> 15:41.875
ETORPHINE HYDROCHLORIDE?

15:41.875 --> 15:45.208
AN ANIMAL TRANQUILIZER
MORE POWERFUL THAN MORPHINE.

15:45.208 --> 15:47.959
IT CAUSES TOTAL PARALYSIS.

15:47.959 --> 15:49.875
THAT MARK ON HER NECK
KEPT BUGGING ME,

15:49.875 --> 15:52.125
SO I ORDERED UP
A TOX SCREEN.

15:52.125 --> 15:55.417
THAT'S IT.
NO MORE DOUGHNUTS FOR MASUKA.

15:55.417 --> 15:57.959
DUDE, THIS STUFF
IS STRICTLY CONTROLLED.

15:57.959 --> 16:01.625
THE ONLY WAY TO GET IT
IS WITH A D.E.A. LICENSE.

16:03.041 --> 16:05.041
I PUT A REQUEST IN
FOR THE LIST.

16:05.041 --> 16:08.083
I SHOULD HAVE IT FOR DOAKES
IN THE MORNING.

16:08.083 --> 16:09.166
NICE.

16:09.166 --> 16:11.875
YEAH, BABY.

16:11.875 --> 16:13.667
I'M ON THAT LIST,

16:13.667 --> 16:17.500
AND EVENTUALLY THE ALIAS I USED
WILL LEAD THEM BACK TO ME.

16:17.500 --> 16:19.125
TICKTOCK.

16:20.500 --> 16:22.792
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

16:25.333 --> 16:26.667
HEY, YOU.

16:26.667 --> 16:28.125
Rita:
Thank God you're there.

16:28.125 --> 16:30.709
I really need to talk
with someone.

16:30.709 --> 16:32.625
EVERYTHING OKAY?

16:32.625 --> 16:34.834
Paul called
after you left.

16:34.834 --> 16:36.417
PAUL? WHO'S PAUL?

16:36.417 --> 16:37.875
MY SOON-TO-BE EX.

16:37.875 --> 16:39.750
HE'S ALREADY OUT OF JAIL --
OVERCROWDING.

16:39.750 --> 16:41.500
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?

16:41.500 --> 16:43.667
Every time something goes just
a little bit right,

16:43.667 --> 16:44.959
something like this happens.

16:44.959 --> 16:46.583
He wants to come
to Astor's party.

16:46.583 --> 16:47.834
WHAT DID YOU TELL HIM?

16:47.834 --> 16:50.875
I'D HAVE TO THINK ABOUT IT.

16:50.875 --> 16:52.959
BUT EVEN IF I SAY "NO,"
HE WON'T LISTEN.

16:52.959 --> 16:55.917
HE NEVER DOES.

16:55.917 --> 16:58.417
CAN YOU --
CAN YOU COME OVER TONIGHT?

16:58.417 --> 17:01.041
I'M KIND OF UNDER THE GUN HERE,
BIG CASE.

17:01.041 --> 17:02.875
I shouldn't be dumping
all this on you.

17:02.875 --> 17:04.041
I'm sorry.

17:04.041 --> 17:05.792
NO, DON'T BE.

17:05.792 --> 17:07.500
TELL YOU WHAT,
I'LL STOP BY IF I CAN.

17:07.500 --> 17:09.000
I PROMISE.

17:09.000 --> 17:12.375
OKAY. I'LL KEEP A PLATE WARM
JUST IN CASE.

17:12.375 --> 17:14.041
THANKS. BYE.

17:16.208 --> 17:18.875
CHECK THE MARINAS.
FIND JORGE CASTILLO'S BOAT.

17:18.875 --> 17:21.041
WE'LL SEARCH THE HOUSE.

17:22.500 --> 17:24.083
WHERE'S LaGUERTA?

17:24.083 --> 17:26.166
TRYING TO BRING THAT KID IN
FOR A SKETCH.

17:26.166 --> 17:28.333
SKETCH?

17:28.333 --> 17:29.959
HE TOLD SOCIAL SERVICES

17:29.959 --> 17:32.834
THAT SOME GUY SAVED HIM
FROM THE BAD LADY.

17:32.834 --> 17:34.417
VALERIE CASTILLO?

17:34.417 --> 17:37.375
SOUNDS LIKE SHE GOT EXACTLY
WHAT SHE HAD COMING TO HER.

17:37.375 --> 17:39.667
PERSONALLY,
I'D SHAKE THIS GUY'S HAND.

17:39.667 --> 17:42.875
YEAH, YOU SAY THAT NOW.

17:52.875 --> 17:56.000
FOUND HIS PASSPORT.

17:56.000 --> 17:57.875
GOD, I FEEL LIKE
I NEED A SHOWER

17:57.875 --> 17:59.625
JUST LOOKING AT
THIS DOUCHE BAG.

17:59.625 --> 18:01.000
WELL, KEEP SEARCHING --

18:01.000 --> 18:03.000
PHONE RECORDS, BANK ACCOUNTS,
CREDIT CARDS.

18:03.000 --> 18:05.750
MAYBE THE WIFE GOT GREEDY,
AND THAT'S WHY HE KILLED HER.

18:05.750 --> 18:07.875
MAYBE.

18:12.500 --> 18:13.917
THIS MORNING
AT THE SALVAGE YARD,

18:13.917 --> 18:15.375
WHAT WAS THAT THING
BY THE CAR?

18:15.375 --> 18:16.750
WHAT THING?

18:16.750 --> 18:19.667
BEFORE YOU OPENED THE TRUNK,
YOU TRIED TO COCKBLOCK ME.

18:19.667 --> 18:21.667
I WAS JUST LOOKING OUT
FOR MY TEAM.

18:21.667 --> 18:23.667
I DIDN'T SEE YOU LOOKING OUT
FOR LaGUERTA.

18:23.667 --> 18:25.125
I WOULD IF SHE'D ASKED.

18:25.125 --> 18:26.291
I DIDN'T ASK.

18:26.291 --> 18:27.709
FINE.

18:27.709 --> 18:29.250
NEXT TIME,
JUST GET YOUR ASS SHOT.

18:31.542 --> 18:33.875
IT'S POSSIBLE
OUR GUY LEFT TOWN.

18:33.875 --> 18:36.125
IF HE EVEN DID IT.

18:37.458 --> 18:39.458
WHAT IF WE HAVE
A COPYCAT KILLER?

18:39.458 --> 18:41.250
THAT'S A BIT OF A STRETCH.

18:41.250 --> 18:43.291
WHAT IF THE PERSON
WHO KILLED VALERIE CASTILLO

18:43.291 --> 18:45.959
WAS TRYING TO BLEED HER OUT
LIKE THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER

18:45.959 --> 18:47.250
BUT DIDN'T KNOW HOW?

18:47.250 --> 18:48.667
SHE WASN'T A HOOKER.

18:48.667 --> 18:50.083
SHE WAS KILLED
SOMEPLACE ELSE

18:50.083 --> 18:51.583
AND LAID OUT
IN A RITUALISTIC MANNER,

18:51.583 --> 18:52.792
JUST LIKE ALL THE OTHERS.

18:52.792 --> 18:53.750
SHE WASN'T IN PIECES.

18:53.750 --> 18:55.375
SHE HAD CUTS ON HER NECK.

18:55.375 --> 18:56.917
I'M JUST SAYING,

18:56.917 --> 19:00.083
WITH ALL THE MEDIA COVERAGE
ON THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER,

19:00.083 --> 19:01.875
IT'S POSSIBLE.

19:01.875 --> 19:03.834
WHAT DO YOU SUGGEST,
MORGAN?

19:03.834 --> 19:06.667
LET ME WORK UP A PROFILE
IN CASE JORGE DOESN'T PAN OUT.

19:08.375 --> 19:09.792
FINE. WHATEVER.

19:09.792 --> 19:11.417
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

19:14.417 --> 19:16.709
THAT'S THE SECOND TIME
YOU'VE MADE THAT FACE.

19:16.709 --> 19:18.583
WHO ARE YOU AVOIDING?

19:20.125 --> 19:22.417
WE GOT ONE MORE STOP
TO MAKE.

19:29.917 --> 19:33.458
NOTHING LASTS FOREVER.

19:33.458 --> 19:35.709
JUST ASK A FORD PINTO.

19:37.166 --> 19:40.417
EVENTUALLY,
MOST SERIAL KILLERS GET CAUGHT.

19:40.417 --> 19:44.250
THERE'S REALLY NOT MUCH
OF A RETIREMENT PLAN.

19:44.250 --> 19:48.291
BUT IT CAN'T END LIKE THIS.
IT'S TOO SOON.

19:48.291 --> 19:49.959
I'M NOT READY.

20:01.333 --> 20:02.959
HE SAW ME.

20:21.750 --> 20:23.291
WHAT'S THIS?

20:23.291 --> 20:25.333
YOU'VE BEEN ASKING
WHO'S BEEN CALLING.

20:25.333 --> 20:27.500
MY MOM LIVES HERE.

20:27.500 --> 20:29.250
DID YOU FORGET
YOUR LAUNDRY?

20:29.250 --> 20:31.583
SHE'S BEEN ON ME
TO STOP BY FOR DINNER.

20:31.583 --> 20:34.333
NOW, HERE'S THE PLAN.
WE GO IN. WE EAT.

20:34.333 --> 20:36.417
WE OUT BEFORE THE CHEESECAKE.
YOU GOT IT?

20:36.417 --> 20:38.000
I'M, WHAT,
YOUR EXIT STRATEGY?

20:38.000 --> 20:40.041
YOU CAN STAY OUT HERE
IF YOU WANT.

20:40.041 --> 20:42.166
THAT GIVES ME A BETTER EXCUSE
TO LEAVE EARLIER,

20:42.166 --> 20:44.333
OR YOU CAN COME IN
AND HAVE SOME FREE FOOD.

20:44.333 --> 20:45.625
IT'S YOUR CALL.

20:45.625 --> 20:46.750
[ SIGHS ]

20:46.750 --> 20:49.083
SHIT.

20:49.083 --> 20:50.250
MY SISTERS ARE HERE, TOO.

20:55.375 --> 20:58.291
FUCKING FAMILY REUNION.

21:00.875 --> 21:02.250
THIS JOHN COMES OUT
OF NOWHERE.

21:02.250 --> 21:03.792
HE'S GOT ME BY THE THROAT.

21:03.792 --> 21:05.083
I CAN'T REACH AROUND
AND GET MY GUN,

21:05.083 --> 21:07.417
AND I SEE HE HAS
A NIPPLE RING.

21:07.417 --> 21:10.208
I RIP THAT FUCKER OUT
LIKE IT'S A GRENADE PIN.

21:10.208 --> 21:11.083
MORGAN.

21:11.083 --> 21:12.875
OH, I'M SORRY.
COP MOUTH.

21:12.875 --> 21:14.417
WE'RE USED TO IT,

21:14.417 --> 21:17.834
WHEN JAMES GRACES HIS FAMILY
WITH THIS PRESENCE.

21:17.834 --> 21:19.625
SOME OF US
DON'T WORK AT A BANK.

21:19.625 --> 21:22.625
FIRST WORDS OUT OF MY
BABY BROTHER'S MOUTH WERE,

21:22.625 --> 21:24.250
"GOT MILK, MOTHERFUCKER?"

21:24.250 --> 21:27.166
OH, OKAY, NOW,
THAT'S ENOUGH, ALL OF YOU.

21:27.166 --> 21:29.083
THAT SECURITY GUARD
IS GONNA BE ALL RIGHT?

21:29.083 --> 21:30.917
IF SOMEONE DID
A HATCHET JOB ON ME,

21:30.917 --> 21:31.959
I'D CASH IT ALL IN.

21:31.959 --> 21:33.458
YEAH, TONY'S DOING OKAY.

21:33.458 --> 21:36.291
THE HOSPITAL'S SETTING HIM UP
WITH SOME PROSTHETICS.

21:36.291 --> 21:39.208
HE'S JUST GOT
THIS SPIRIT ABOUT HIM.

21:39.208 --> 21:40.792
THE GUY'S MISSING BODY PARTS

21:40.792 --> 21:42.458
BECAUSE OF THIS
ICE-TRUCK KILLER,

21:42.458 --> 21:44.500
AND HE'S STILL
HITTING ON ME.

21:44.500 --> 21:47.792
THAT'S BECAUSE MEN ONLY THINK
WITH ONE BODY PART,

21:47.792 --> 21:49.834
AND THAT ONE
WAS NOT CUT OFF.

21:49.834 --> 21:51.291
MA!

21:51.291 --> 21:52.875
WELL, IT'S THE DAMN TRUTH.

21:52.875 --> 21:55.125
MORGAN, COME ON.
WE GOT A CASE TO SOLVE.

21:55.125 --> 21:56.583
OH, ARE YOU SURE, HONEY?

21:56.583 --> 21:58.583
I GOT SOME CHEESECAKE
IN THE FRIDGE.

21:58.583 --> 22:01.083
YEAH. WE'RE SURE.

22:01.083 --> 22:03.166
YOU KNOW...

22:03.166 --> 22:05.041
I WOULD LOVE
SOME CHEESECAKE.

22:05.041 --> 22:07.125
YOU CAN WAIT IN THE CAR.
THAT'S YOUR CALL.

22:07.125 --> 22:08.083
[ LAUGHTER ]

22:08.083 --> 22:10.750
HE'LL WAIT.

22:10.750 --> 22:13.125
I'LL HELP YOU.
OOH, I'M SORRY.

22:13.125 --> 22:16.375
[ LAUGHTER CONTINUES ]

22:16.375 --> 22:19.500
I WONDER, IN TIME,
IF THEY'LL EVEN REMEMBER ME,

22:19.500 --> 22:23.375
OTHER THAN THE MAN
WHO BROKE THEIR MOTHER'S HEART.

22:23.375 --> 22:27.041
I'LL BE BREAKING
THEIR HEARTS, TOO.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.875
Rita:
HE IS THEIR FATHER.

22:28.875 --> 22:31.875
THEY HAVE A RIGHT TO KNOW
HE'S BEEN RELEASED, RIGHT?

22:31.875 --> 22:35.291
YEAH, SURE.

22:35.291 --> 22:37.542
EVEN IF I TELL PAUL
NOT TO COME,

22:37.542 --> 22:39.750
HE'LL SHOW UP HERE
EVENTUALLY.

22:39.750 --> 22:41.333
I KNOW HIM.

22:41.333 --> 22:44.208
EVERYTHING'S
BEEN GOING SO GOOD AT WORK...

22:44.208 --> 22:47.542
WITH YOU.

22:47.542 --> 22:49.125
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

22:49.125 --> 22:52.000
HE'S REALLY GOT A HOLD ON YOU,
DOESN'T HE?

22:54.333 --> 22:59.000
PAUL ALWAYS HAD A TEMPER,
BUT WHEN HE WAS USING...

22:59.000 --> 23:00.875
HE SAID IF I LEFT,

23:00.875 --> 23:03.000
HE WOULD FIND US
AND HURT THE KIDS.

23:03.000 --> 23:05.583
SOMEHOW,
I THOUGHT THAT BY STAYING,

23:05.583 --> 23:07.333
I WAS PROTECTING THEM.

23:09.291 --> 23:12.375
CODY DOESN'T REMEMBER
THE WORST OF IT,

23:12.375 --> 23:13.542
BUT ASTOR...

23:15.750 --> 23:19.041
SHE WAS THE ONE WHO CALLED
THE POLICE THE LAST TIME.

23:19.041 --> 23:20.917
SHE WAS PROTECTING ME.

23:22.959 --> 23:24.333
YOU'RE NOT THAT WOMAN
ANYMORE.

23:24.333 --> 23:27.625
YOU'RE STRONGER
THAN THAT NOW.

23:27.625 --> 23:30.041
IF THEIR DAD SHOWS UP,
WE'LL DEAL WITH IT TOGETHER.

23:31.667 --> 23:33.834
DAD'S COMING HOME?

23:39.166 --> 23:41.917
CAN HE SLEEP IN MY ROOM,
MOM?

23:41.917 --> 23:42.875
CAN HE, MOM?

23:42.875 --> 23:45.291
I SHOULDN'T EVEN BE HERE.

23:45.291 --> 23:47.625
RITA WILL BE DEVASTATED
IF I'M ARRESTED.

23:47.625 --> 23:49.375
HER HUSBAND WAS A CRACKHEAD,

23:49.375 --> 23:51.041
AND HER BOYFRIEND'S
A SERIAL KILLER.

23:51.041 --> 23:53.583
IT'S KIND OF HARD
NOT TO TAKE THAT PERSONALLY.

23:58.500 --> 24:01.458
BETTER GET INSIDE, SON.
STORM'S ON ITS WAY.

24:01.458 --> 24:04.208
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

24:30.959 --> 24:32.125
AAH!

24:41.417 --> 24:44.125
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
WHAT YOU ARE, DEX?

25:11.750 --> 25:13.667
ANY LAST WORDS?

25:15.583 --> 25:17.792
FIGURES.

25:23.333 --> 25:25.667
[ GASPS ]

25:32.458 --> 25:35.375
I DON'T HAVE BAD DREAMS.

25:35.375 --> 25:37.667
WHEN I SLEEP, ALL OF ME SLEEPS.

25:37.667 --> 25:40.542
NOTHING EVER GOES BUMP
IN DEXTER'S NIGHT.

25:47.000 --> 25:52.333
I'VE NEVER FELT A MOMENT
OF REMORSE, DOUBT, REGRET.

25:56.291 --> 25:58.333
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?

26:02.500 --> 26:04.750
IF MY BACK WASN'T AGAINST
THE WALL,

26:04.750 --> 26:08.291
I'D ALMOST FEEL GUILTY FOR
HACKING INTO MASUKA'S E-MAIL.

26:08.291 --> 26:10.834
ONCE I GOT PAST ALL THE PORN,
IT WAS EASY.

26:13.000 --> 26:16.000
AND THERE I AM.

26:16.000 --> 26:18.208
DR. PATRICK BATEMAN --

26:18.208 --> 26:21.625
SO WHOLESOME, SO INCONSPICUOUS.

26:21.625 --> 26:23.709
HARRY WOULD FROWN UPON
DESTROYING EVIDENCE,

26:23.709 --> 26:26.083
BUT HE NEVER WANTED ME
TO GET CAUGHT, EITHER.

26:26.083 --> 26:28.125
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN HERE?

26:28.125 --> 26:30.375
MY COMPUTER WENT DOWN.

26:30.375 --> 26:31.750
I WAS JUST CHECKING
SOME E-MAIL.

26:34.250 --> 26:36.375
CAN YOU TAKE A LOOK
AT THIS FOR ME?

26:38.041 --> 26:39.709
COPYCAT KILLER?

26:39.709 --> 26:41.542
I WORKED ALL NIGHT
ON THAT PROFILE.

26:41.542 --> 26:43.125
I'D LIKE TO GIVE IT
TO LaGUERTA,

26:43.125 --> 26:44.583
BUT I WANT TO MAKE SURE
IT'S GOOD ENOUGH.

26:44.583 --> 26:47.250
I'M HONORED.

26:48.667 --> 26:51.667
"THE SIMILAR MANNER IN WHICH
THE BODY WAS DISPLAYED

26:51.667 --> 26:54.542
"SUGGESTS THIS KILLER
FEELS A CONNECTION

26:54.542 --> 26:56.250
"TO THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER,

26:56.250 --> 26:58.875
EXCITED BY WHAT
HE'S DOING."

27:03.792 --> 27:06.709
"THE CUT ON THE VICTIM'S CHEEK,
WHILE NOT FATAL,

27:06.709 --> 27:09.083
"APPEARS TO BE A SIGNATURE
OF SORTS.

27:09.083 --> 27:11.083
"BECAUSE OF THE LACK
OF EVIDENCE

27:11.083 --> 27:13.083
"COLLECTED FROM
THE CRIME SCENE,

27:13.083 --> 27:15.834
"THE SUSPECT MAY BE FAMILIAR
WITH LAW ENFORCEMENT

27:15.834 --> 27:18.083
OR FORENSICS PROCEDURE."

27:20.041 --> 27:20.959
OH.

27:20.959 --> 27:22.250
WHY'D YOU QUIT?

27:22.250 --> 27:23.750
YOU'RE GETTING TO
THE GOOD STUFF.

27:23.750 --> 27:25.041
LET ME GUESS --

27:25.041 --> 27:26.542
SINGLE WHITE MALE, MID-30s,
LIVES ALONE,

27:26.542 --> 27:28.959
DISCONNECTED
FROM HIS EMOTIONS.

27:31.208 --> 27:33.333
IT'S A LITTLE TEXTBOOK,
DON'T YOU THINK?

27:33.333 --> 27:35.458
BUT IT TOTALLY FITS
THIS CASE.

27:35.458 --> 27:37.166
YOU'RE TRYING
TO MAKE IT FIT.

27:38.542 --> 27:40.375
[ SIGHS ]

27:40.375 --> 27:42.291
MY ADVICE?

27:42.291 --> 27:43.834
KEEP THIS TO YOURSELF.

27:46.083 --> 27:47.125
REALLY?

27:47.125 --> 27:48.458
DEB, YOU'RE NEW
TO HOMICIDE.

27:48.458 --> 27:49.959
THIS BLOWS UP
IN YOUR FACE,

27:49.959 --> 27:52.041
YOU'VE GIVEN LaGUERTA
THE EXCUSE

27:52.041 --> 27:53.375
TO SEND YOU BACK TO VICE.

28:01.083 --> 28:02.291
NO.

28:02.291 --> 28:05.125
I'M ON TO SOMETHING HERE.
I FEEL IT.

28:05.125 --> 28:06.959
LIKE ONE OF YOUR HUNCHES.

28:10.458 --> 28:13.333
WAY TO HAVE MY BACK.

28:19.792 --> 28:21.208
WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?

28:24.875 --> 28:27.709
DEBRA, WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

28:32.041 --> 28:33.792
HOW DID YOU
GET INTO MY CABINET?

28:33.792 --> 28:37.959
YOU HIDE THE KEY IN THE PANTRY
ON THE TOP SHELF.

28:37.959 --> 28:42.333
YOU AND YOUR BROTHER KNOW
NEVER TO TOUCH MY GUNS

28:42.333 --> 28:44.542
UNLESS IT'S UNDER
MY DIRECT SUPERVISION.

28:44.542 --> 28:46.375
BUT I WAS BEING
REALLY CAREFUL.

28:46.375 --> 28:48.500
I MEAN, I WAS ONLY SHOOTING
AT THE CANS AND THE BOTTLES.

28:48.500 --> 28:50.500
AND I'M REALLY GOOD,
LIKE DEXTER,

28:50.500 --> 28:53.500
AND NOW WE CAN ALL
GO HUNTING TOGETHER.

28:53.500 --> 28:55.375
I'M DISAPPOINTED IN YOU,
DEBRA.

28:56.583 --> 28:58.166
GRAB YOUR THINGS.

29:05.000 --> 29:06.875
THANKS A LOT.

29:09.417 --> 29:11.250
Doakes:
STARTING THIS MORNING,

29:11.250 --> 29:13.041
WE HAVE CADETS
FROM THE ACADEMY

29:13.041 --> 29:15.458
GOING OVER EVERY INCH
OF THE SALVAGE YARD.

29:15.458 --> 29:16.500
THOSE DAYS I DON'T MISS.

29:16.500 --> 29:18.166
THE KID
WE FOUND YESTERDAY

29:18.166 --> 29:20.375
SAW SOMEONE ABDUCT
VALERIE CASTILLO.

29:20.375 --> 29:23.208
BECAUSE HE DIDN'T RECOGNIZE
A PHOTO OF JORGE CASTILLO,

29:23.208 --> 29:25.166
LIEUTENANT LaGUERTA
IS BRINGING HIM IN

29:25.166 --> 29:26.792
TO ATTEMPT A SKETCH.

29:30.250 --> 29:31.542
COME ON, SWEETHEART.

29:31.542 --> 29:34.166
LET'S TAKE
THE SEATBELT OFF.

29:34.166 --> 29:36.250
THERE YOU GO.
COME ON.

29:36.250 --> 29:37.875
COME ON, SWEETHEART.

29:37.875 --> 29:39.792
YOU WANT TO GO INSIDE
TO SEE THE NICE LADY?

29:39.792 --> 29:42.208
COME ON, SWEETIE.
LET'S GO.

29:43.583 --> 29:45.041
THANKS
FOR BRINGING HIM BY.

29:51.291 --> 29:52.583
HOLA, OSCAR.

29:52.583 --> 29:55.583
¿Tú QUIERES VENIR CONMIGO?

29:57.542 --> 30:00.083
NORMALLY, I WOULDN'T APPROVE
OF SOMETHING LIKE THIS,

30:00.083 --> 30:02.625
BUT YOU'VE MADE QUITE
AN IMPRESSION.

30:04.875 --> 30:06.083
YOU HAVE KIDS?

30:06.083 --> 30:08.333
NO.

30:09.500 --> 30:11.083
I WAS LIKE HIM ONCE --

30:11.083 --> 30:13.542
A STRANGER
IN A STRANGE PLACE,

30:13.542 --> 30:16.375
LEFT TO GROW UP
WITH STRANGERS,

30:16.375 --> 30:17.750
ALL FOR A BETTER LIFE.

30:19.417 --> 30:22.583
WELL, POLICE LIEUTENANT --
I'D SAY YOU'VE DONE OKAY.

30:22.583 --> 30:25.333
ANY LUCK
WITH THE FAMILY?

30:25.333 --> 30:27.542
NO. HE TALKS ABOUT
AN UNCLE ROBERTO.

30:27.542 --> 30:29.250
HE JUST USES
THE FIRST NAME.

30:29.250 --> 30:31.291
MAYBE WE'LL HAVE SOME LUCK
ON OUR END.

30:31.291 --> 30:32.875
I HOPE SO.

30:32.875 --> 30:34.959
I HATE TO SEND ANOTHER ONE
INTO FOSTER CARE.

30:37.959 --> 30:38.959
THANK YOU.

30:38.959 --> 30:41.166
BYE, SWEETHEART.

30:43.000 --> 30:45.291
MEANWHILE, WE'LL FOLLOW UP
ON THE D.E.A. LIST

30:45.291 --> 30:47.041
OF M-99 BUYERS.

30:47.041 --> 30:49.417
THAT WOULD INCLUDE VETS,
DOCTORS,

30:49.417 --> 30:52.750
ANIMAL CONTROL,
EVEN CIRCUSES.

30:52.750 --> 30:55.333
BE THOROUGH.
CHECK EVERYONE.

30:55.333 --> 30:58.417
MASUKA, WHAT DO WE HAVE
ON THE HOME AND THE BOAT?

30:58.417 --> 31:00.500
STILL PROCESSING, SIR.

31:00.500 --> 31:02.125
IF THE HUSBAND
IS A DEAD END,

31:02.125 --> 31:04.709
THEN WE'RE LOOKING AT
A NEW SUSPECT, FOLKS.

31:04.709 --> 31:08.375
MORGAN, ANY IDEAS?

31:08.375 --> 31:09.792
DON'T DO IT, DEB.

31:09.792 --> 31:11.500
THE LAST THING
I NEED RIGHT NOW

31:11.500 --> 31:14.625
IS TO BE PROFILED
FOR ALL OF MIAMI METRO.

31:14.625 --> 31:16.250
WE COULD BE LOOKING
AT SOMEONE

31:16.250 --> 31:18.208
WHO'S INSPIRED
BY THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER.

31:18.208 --> 31:20.500
IF SO, THE SUSPECT
IS PROBABLY FAMILIAR

31:20.500 --> 31:22.000
WITH FORENSIC PROCEDURES.

31:22.000 --> 31:24.166
I HAVE A PROFILE.
I'D BE HAPPY TO SHOW IT TO YOU.

31:24.166 --> 31:25.667
I'LL BE IN MY LAB.

31:27.792 --> 31:29.208
HELLO, DEX.

31:39.417 --> 31:42.458
Batista: OSCAR...

31:42.458 --> 31:47.166
¿EL HOMBRE QUE VISTE
ERA COMO YO O MáS DELGADO?

31:50.917 --> 31:53.250
MI HIJITO, ESTá BIEN.
CUéNTANOS.

31:53.250 --> 31:55.917
CUéNTANOS LO QUE Tú VISTE
ESA NOCHE.

32:01.333 --> 32:02.834
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

32:02.834 --> 32:03.875
NO.

32:11.667 --> 32:13.875
[ WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY ]

32:17.709 --> 32:19.250
ESTá BIEN,
ME QUEDO AQUí.

32:19.250 --> 32:20.875
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

32:27.750 --> 32:31.166
I FORGOT HOW MUCH I LOVED
PASTELITOS GROWING UP.

32:31.166 --> 32:33.542
HE JUST NEEDED
A LITTLE REMINDER OF HOME.

32:33.542 --> 32:34.875
I WAS BARELY HIS AGE

32:34.875 --> 32:36.709
WHEN I CAME OVER
WITH MY FAMILY.

32:36.709 --> 32:38.875
I THREW UP
THE WHOLE DAMN WAY.

32:40.750 --> 32:43.417
¿QUIERES MáS?

32:43.417 --> 32:44.375
MM-HMM.

32:44.375 --> 32:47.625
¿CINCO?
[ LAUGHS ]

32:47.625 --> 32:50.000
GO GET THE ARTIST.
I THINK SOMEBODY'S READY.

32:50.000 --> 32:51.667
SAVE ME SOME.

32:53.333 --> 32:55.834
NO, DICE QUE NO.

32:55.834 --> 32:59.250
CINCO NO PUEDE.
PERO TRES, Sí.

32:59.250 --> 33:00.667
NO ES 5, ES 10.

33:00.667 --> 33:02.875
¿10?  [ LAUGHS ]

33:02.875 --> 33:04.583
TE DIGO QUE Tú HABLAS
CON EL SEÑOR

33:04.583 --> 33:06.250
CUANDO EL VENGA,

33:06.250 --> 33:08.375
Y ENTONCES, Sí, YO TE DOY 10,
LO QUE Tú QUIERAS.

33:08.375 --> 33:11.500
20. 30.

33:11.500 --> 33:13.208
50.

33:13.208 --> 33:15.792
[ LAUGHS ]

33:23.917 --> 33:26.000
DID YOU THANK MRS. CARROLL

33:26.000 --> 33:28.125
FOR PICKING YOU UP
FROM SCHOOL FOR ME?

33:28.125 --> 33:30.166
YES.

33:36.083 --> 33:39.291
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

33:42.250 --> 33:43.792
EVERYTHING OKAY?

33:43.792 --> 33:46.125
YOU WANT TO TALK
ABOUT IT?

33:46.125 --> 33:49.542
HOLLY, BLAKE, AND ASHLEY SAID
THEY CAN'T COME TO MY PARTY.

33:49.542 --> 33:51.000
HONEY, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

33:51.000 --> 33:52.792
I SPOKE WITH THEIR MOMS
LAST WEEK.

33:52.792 --> 33:54.208
IT'S ALL CODY'S FAULT.

33:54.208 --> 33:55.792
HE COULDN'T KEEP
HIS MOUTH SHUT

33:55.792 --> 33:57.208
ABOUT DAD GETTING OUT
OF JAIL.

33:57.208 --> 33:58.500
DID NOT!

33:58.500 --> 34:00.959
YOU TOLD EVERYONE!

34:10.667 --> 34:12.083
Dexter:
I HAVE TO KNOW.

34:18.041 --> 34:20.917
DEXTER...

34:20.917 --> 34:22.667
THANK GOD.

34:22.667 --> 34:25.250
MY ARM'S ASLEEP.

34:25.250 --> 34:27.458
HOW LONG HAVE YOU TWO
BEEN LIKE THIS?

34:27.458 --> 34:29.083
HALF AN HOUR.

34:29.083 --> 34:31.834
I WAS AFRAID I'D WAKE HIM
IF I MOVED.

34:33.417 --> 34:34.750
AT THAT AGE,

34:34.750 --> 34:37.166
WHEN THEY'RE OUT,
THEY'RE OUT.

34:37.166 --> 34:40.208
YOU COULD BRUSH HIS TEETH,
AND HE WOULDN'T WAKE UP.

34:41.625 --> 34:42.959
HERE.
LIFT UP HIS HEAD.

34:42.959 --> 34:45.083
I'LL SLIDE THIS
UNDERNEATH.

35:01.041 --> 35:03.750
OH, THANKS.

35:05.792 --> 35:08.250
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

35:08.250 --> 35:09.917
I'M WAITING ON
SOME LAB WORK.

35:09.917 --> 35:11.250
I HAD SOME TIME TO KILL.

35:13.333 --> 35:15.542
GO AHEAD.
WE DIDN'T GET VERY FAR.

35:15.542 --> 35:16.750
HE'S SO TIRED.

35:16.750 --> 35:19.333
WE'RE GONNA PICK IT UP AGAIN
TOMORROW.

35:19.333 --> 35:22.041
IT'S ONLY A MATTER OF TIME

35:22.041 --> 35:25.375
BEFORE WE KNOW
WHAT THIS LITTLE GUY SAW.

35:45.458 --> 35:48.875
COME ON.

35:48.875 --> 35:51.583
[ GROANS ]

35:53.125 --> 35:55.041
[ SIGHS ]

35:55.041 --> 35:56.667
OW.

35:59.417 --> 36:03.041
IF YOU, UM...HERE.

36:03.041 --> 36:04.917
YOU WANT HELP OR NOT?

36:06.917 --> 36:10.458
I HAVE A HAIR OR SOMETHING
STUCK ON MY LENS.

36:10.458 --> 36:12.125
YOU'RE IN GOOD HANDS.

36:12.125 --> 36:14.458
I TRADED MY GLASSES IN
FOR CONTACTS IN HIGH SCHOOL.

36:14.458 --> 36:15.458
BOYS?

36:15.458 --> 36:17.458
YEAH. WHAT I REALLY NEEDED
WAS TITS.

36:17.458 --> 36:19.792
I HAD WINNIE THE POOHS
ON MY BRAS UNTIL I WAS 16.

36:19.792 --> 36:23.000
AS YOU CAN SEE, NOT A WHOLE
LOT'S CHANGED SINCE THEN.

36:23.000 --> 36:24.625
TRY NOT TO BLINK, OKAY?

36:26.625 --> 36:28.583
OKAY, OKAY.
I'LL DO IT.

36:28.583 --> 36:31.000
I'LL DO IT.

36:31.000 --> 36:33.750
LET ME
ASK YOU SOMETHING.

36:33.750 --> 36:36.000
YOUR BROTHER'S ADOPTED,
RIGHT?

36:36.000 --> 36:38.125
YEAH, MY DAD FOUND HIM
AT A CRIME SCENE.

36:38.125 --> 36:40.250
HOW DID THE DEPARTMENT FEEL
ABOUT HARRY

36:40.250 --> 36:42.083
GETTING PERSONALLY INVOLVED
IN A CASE?

36:42.083 --> 36:43.500
IT DIDN'T SEEM TO BE
A PROBLEM.

36:43.500 --> 36:44.959
MY PARENTS NEVER
TALKED ABOUT IT.

36:44.959 --> 36:46.542
OH, BUT STILL,
RAISING A BOY,

36:46.542 --> 36:48.166
IT'S A LOT OF WORK, NO?

36:48.166 --> 36:49.375
DEX?

36:49.375 --> 36:50.375
GOD, NO.

36:50.375 --> 36:51.917
I GOT IN MORE TROUBLE
THAN HE DID.

36:51.917 --> 36:53.291
HE WAS THE PERFECT ONE.

36:53.291 --> 36:55.166
HERE, I THINK I SEE IT.

36:56.750 --> 36:58.208
YEAH.

36:58.208 --> 37:00.750
THERE'S THE BASTARD.

37:03.333 --> 37:04.417
THANKS.

37:04.417 --> 37:05.500
MM-HMM.

37:06.834 --> 37:10.709
[ FAUCET RUNS ]

37:10.709 --> 37:12.000
LET ME ASK YOU
A QUESTION.

37:13.750 --> 37:15.375
WHY DO YOU
HAVE IT IN FOR ME?

37:17.500 --> 37:19.291
YOU'RE LOUD,
YOU'RE IMPULSIVE,

37:19.291 --> 37:21.375
AND YOU CONSTANTLY
QUESTION AUTHORITY.

37:22.959 --> 37:24.375
FAIR ENOUGH.

37:26.375 --> 37:28.542
I HEAR YOU HAVE
AN INTERESTING THEORY ON --

37:28.542 --> 37:30.000
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

37:34.875 --> 37:38.333
Man:
The report on scandal-plagued
AFL's transactions in Florida

37:38.333 --> 37:40.208
showed Transportation Department
employees

37:40.208 --> 37:43.208
received more than
$460 in gifts,

37:43.208 --> 37:45.125
ranging from golf balls
and free dinners...

37:45.125 --> 37:46.375
HONEY, WHAT IS IT?

37:46.375 --> 37:48.083
...several local retailers

37:48.083 --> 37:50.125
in return for buying supplies
worth $7,000...

37:50.125 --> 37:51.291
[ TELEVISION CLICKS OFF ]

37:55.375 --> 37:57.208
SWEETIE.

37:57.208 --> 37:59.542
I'M SORRY.
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

37:59.542 --> 38:02.208
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
THESE THINGS HAPPEN.

38:02.208 --> 38:05.208
GO GET CHANGED,
AND I'LL FIX THE BED.

38:12.834 --> 38:15.333
MOMMY?

38:15.333 --> 38:18.834
IS IT OKAY
IF I DIDN'T HAVE MY PARTY?

38:50.750 --> 38:53.125
IT'S ONLY A MATTER OF TIME

38:53.125 --> 38:55.375
BEFORE THAT BOY
FINISHES TELLING THE POLICE

38:55.375 --> 38:59.542
WHO HE SAW THAT NIGHT
AT THE SALVAGE YARD -- ME.

38:59.542 --> 39:01.208
ONCE THE SKETCH IS FINISHED,

39:01.208 --> 39:04.000
THERE WILL BE
NO PLACE LEFT TO HIDE.

39:04.000 --> 39:05.792
IF I WANT ANY CHANCE
OF SURVIVAL,

39:05.792 --> 39:08.375
I HAVE TO GET RID OF IT ALL.

39:08.375 --> 39:10.500
I HAVE TO LET GO.

39:47.834 --> 39:50.834
ALEX TIMMONS -- SNIPER.

39:50.834 --> 39:53.667
YES, I DID IT.

39:53.667 --> 39:55.417
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT
TO HEAR?

39:57.917 --> 40:00.542
GENE MARSHALL -- ARSONIST.

40:00.542 --> 40:03.917
HAVE YOU EVER WATCHED SOMEONE
BURNED ALIVE?

40:05.250 --> 40:08.583
CINDY LANDON -- BLACK WIDOW.

40:08.583 --> 40:11.125
I'LL FUCK YOU
IF YOU LET ME GO.

40:11.125 --> 40:13.917
SUCH FOND MEMORIES OF THEM ALL.

40:13.917 --> 40:17.208
THEY ALL ACCEPTED THEIR FATE
IN THEIR OWN WAY.

40:17.208 --> 40:19.583
NOW IT'S TIME FOR ME
TO DO THE SAME.

40:19.583 --> 40:22.959
VALERIE CASTILLO --
MY LAST VICTIM.

40:31.875 --> 40:33.667
HE'S NOT ANGRY.

40:33.667 --> 40:36.375
THAT'S NOT WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

40:36.375 --> 40:38.458
HE'S TESTING ME.

40:40.542 --> 40:42.875
I WAS WRONG THE WHOLE TIME.

40:42.875 --> 40:45.917
MY PLAYMATE SAW AN OPPORTUNITY
TO PAINT ME INTO A CORNER

40:45.917 --> 40:48.291
TO SEE IF I'D FIND MY WAY OUT,

40:48.291 --> 40:50.208
IF I'D FIGHT TO SURVIVE.

41:17.041 --> 41:19.083
IF YOU HAVE
A WELL-PRESERVED SAMPLE,

41:19.083 --> 41:22.709
TRANSFERRING A DRY DROP
OF BLOOD IS RELATIVELY EASY,

41:22.709 --> 41:24.542
ALMOST AS EASY AS IT WAS

41:24.542 --> 41:26.709
LIFTING JORGE CASTILLO'S
FINGERPRINTS FROM HIS BOAT

41:26.709 --> 41:28.917
AND PUTTING THEM ON THIS KNIFE.

42:00.959 --> 42:02.875
JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH THE FBI.

42:02.875 --> 42:04.458
NOW FOR THE HARD PART.

42:04.458 --> 42:06.667
I WANTED TO SEE WHAT THEIR
COMPUTERS WOULD SPIT OUT.

42:06.667 --> 42:09.500
I CROSS-REFERENCED MY PROFILE
WITH THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER LIST.

42:09.500 --> 42:11.041
11 NEW HITS.

42:11.041 --> 42:13.792
HOW ABOUT WE HOLD OFF
TILL WE GET A SKETCH,

42:13.792 --> 42:15.834
TAKE IT FROM THERE.

42:15.834 --> 42:17.125
I KNOW, I KNOW.

42:17.125 --> 42:18.500
I WANT TO GET
A HEAD START ON THIS.

42:18.500 --> 42:21.166
WE COULD LOOK THESE OVER
AT LUNCH -- MY TREAT.

42:21.166 --> 42:22.250
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

42:22.250 --> 42:25.291
YOU NEVER GIVE UP,
DO YOU?

42:25.291 --> 42:27.709
THANK YOUR MOM FOR DINNER
THE OTHER NIGHT.

42:27.709 --> 42:30.333
CAN'T REMEMBER THE LAST TIME
I MET A GUY'S FAMILY

42:30.333 --> 42:31.542
AND THEY ACTUALLY LIKED ME.

42:31.542 --> 42:33.166
YOU HELD YOUR OWN.

42:33.166 --> 42:34.834
MOST PEOPLE DON'T GET
A DIRTY WORD IN EDGEWISE

42:34.834 --> 42:36.667
WITH MY SISTERS
AROUND THE TABLE.

42:36.667 --> 42:39.417
IN OUR HOUSE, EVERY THURSDAY
NIGHT WAS PANCAKE NIGHT --

42:39.417 --> 42:42.166
MORGAN TRADITION.

42:42.166 --> 42:44.166
I MISS THAT KIND OF STUFF,
YOU KNOW?

42:44.166 --> 42:45.583
I FOUND SOMETHING.

42:47.333 --> 42:49.041
THE WIFE'S BLOOD?
YOU'RE SURE?

42:49.041 --> 42:51.709
THIS WAS FOUND IN
THE CASTILLO'S BEDROOM HAMPER.

42:51.709 --> 42:53.500
WE CHECK ALL THE CLOTHING ITEMS
THAT COME IN.

42:53.500 --> 42:55.667
BECAUSE OF SHEER VOLUME,
THAT TAKES TIME.

42:55.667 --> 42:57.000
IT DOESN'T PROVE ANYTHING.

42:57.000 --> 42:58.500
NOT BY ITSELF.

42:58.500 --> 43:00.291
I'VE BEEN RE-EXAMINING
THE VIDEO FOOTAGE

43:00.291 --> 43:02.333
I TOOK FROM THAT MORNING.

43:02.333 --> 43:04.375
NOTICE THE CUTS ALONG
THE CAROTID ARTERIES.

43:04.375 --> 43:05.875
THEY'RE LONG AND DEEP.

43:05.875 --> 43:07.291
VALERIE CASTILLO
BLED TO DEATH IN MINUTES.

43:07.291 --> 43:08.208
NO SHIT.

43:08.208 --> 43:09.875
THE PERSON WHO DID THIS

43:09.875 --> 43:12.000
WASN'T TRYING TO EMULATE
THE ICE-TRUCK KILLER.

43:12.000 --> 43:13.834
HE WAS...IN A HURRY.

43:13.834 --> 43:15.959
HE WAS PROBABLY AFRAID
OF GETTING CAUGHT.

43:15.959 --> 43:17.542
MOST KILLERS ARE.

43:17.542 --> 43:20.166
EXCEPT IF THIS WAS A COPYCAT,
HE WOULDN'T BE IN A RUSH.

43:20.166 --> 43:22.542
HE WOULD SAVOR
HIS FIRST KILL.

43:22.542 --> 43:24.542
HE WOULD CONTROL
THE PRECISE MOMENT

43:24.542 --> 43:26.041
VALERIE CASTILLO DIED

43:26.041 --> 43:28.083
INSTEAD OF JUST LETTING HER
BLEED OUT.

43:28.083 --> 43:31.750
THIS IS ALL TOO...

43:31.750 --> 43:34.875
PASSIVE.

43:34.875 --> 43:37.291
HAVE YOU COMPLETELY RULED OUT
THE HUSBAND?

43:37.291 --> 43:39.375
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

43:39.375 --> 43:41.500
THE BOY SAID HE DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE JORGE CASTILLO

43:41.500 --> 43:43.041
IN ANY OF THE PHOTOS.

43:43.041 --> 43:44.875
HE WAS A DEHYDRATED
AND TRAUMATIZED 7-YEAR-OLD

43:44.875 --> 43:47.208
LEFT TO FEND FOR HIMSELF
FOR DAYS IN A SALVAGE YARD.

43:47.208 --> 43:49.250
YOU REALLY THINK
IT'S THE HUSBAND?

43:49.250 --> 43:52.000
HE'S A DEEP-SEA FISHERMAN.
MOST KNOW HOW TO USE A KNIFE.

43:52.000 --> 43:53.583
PLUS, HE'S STILL MISSING.

43:56.917 --> 43:59.291
HAVE YOU FINISHED YOUR SEARCH
OF THE SALVAGE YARD?

44:00.583 --> 44:02.583
I'LL HAVE THEM SEND
THE CADETS OUT AGAIN.

44:05.458 --> 44:07.000
HEY, I'M SORRY.

44:07.000 --> 44:09.542
[ SIGHS ]

44:09.542 --> 44:11.709
I KNOW HOW HARD YOU WORKED
ON THAT PROFILE.

44:11.709 --> 44:13.667
NO, DEX, I REALLY
DON'T THINK YOU DO.

44:17.959 --> 44:20.166
[ SIGHS ]

44:25.917 --> 44:29.166
HOW LONG
ARE YOU GROUNDED FOR?

44:29.166 --> 44:31.125
TWO MONTHS.

44:33.250 --> 44:35.792
DEB, I HAD TO TELL HIM.

44:35.792 --> 44:37.667
NO, DEX, YOU DIDN'T.

44:37.667 --> 44:40.458
YOU COULD HAVE KEPT
YOUR FUCKING MOUTH SHUT.

44:40.458 --> 44:42.542
DAD WAS WORRIED ABOUT YOU,
AND SO WAS I.

44:42.542 --> 44:45.333
WELL, NOW YOU CAN SPEND
MORE TIME TOGETHER.

44:45.333 --> 44:48.208
I'M NOT STUPID, DEXTER.
THAT'S ALWAYS WHAT YOU WANTED.

44:48.208 --> 44:51.333
NO, IT'S NOT.

44:51.333 --> 44:53.333
DEB, YOU'RE MY SISTER.

44:53.333 --> 44:55.458
NO, I AM NOT.

44:55.458 --> 44:58.000
AND HE IS MY FATHER.

44:58.000 --> 44:59.917
THERE ARE SO MANY TIMES,
I SWEAR, DEXTER,

44:59.917 --> 45:02.834
THAT I WISH HE WOULD HAVE
NEVER BROUGHT YOU HOME.

45:06.333 --> 45:09.166
DEXTER,
I AM SO SORRY.

45:09.166 --> 45:12.750
I REALLY, REALLY
DIDN'T MEAN IT LIKE THAT.

45:18.250 --> 45:19.750
HERE.

45:21.625 --> 45:23.750
I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT WANT THAT.

45:24.834 --> 45:27.000
YOU'RE A BETTER SHOT
THAN ME ANYWAY.

45:52.500 --> 45:56.792
[ BEEPING ]

45:56.792 --> 45:59.417
[ Ringing ]

46:02.250 --> 46:03.792
Paul: Hello?

46:03.792 --> 46:05.792
PAUL, HEY, IT'S ME.

46:05.792 --> 46:08.166
LOOK,
WE NEED TO TALK.

46:08.166 --> 46:09.291
Sure thing.

46:09.291 --> 46:11.625
I KNOW YOU WANT
TO SEE ASTOR,

46:11.625 --> 46:13.667
BUT, I MEAN,

46:13.667 --> 46:16.208
THE KIDS ARE DOING
SO WELL NOW.

46:16.208 --> 46:18.834
MAYBE IT WOULD BE
A GOOD IDEA

46:18.834 --> 46:22.208
IF YOU DON'T COME
TO THE PARTY.

46:22.208 --> 46:24.166
She is my daughter,
too, Rita.

46:24.166 --> 46:26.208
I have every right
to be there.

46:26.208 --> 46:27.667
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M SORRY.

46:27.667 --> 46:30.041
I'M SORRY,
BUT I HAVE FULL CUSTODY NOW,

46:30.041 --> 46:32.709
AND YOU CAN'T JUST DROP IN
ON US LIKE THIS ANYMORE.

46:32.709 --> 46:34.125
NOW, I CHECKED.

46:34.125 --> 46:35.834
THE RESTRAINING ORDER
IS STILL IN EFFECT.

46:35.834 --> 46:37.917
IF YOU STEP ONE FOOT
ON THIS PROPERTY,

46:37.917 --> 46:39.834
THE FIRST CALL I'M GONNA MAKE
IS TO THE POLICE.

46:39.834 --> 46:41.959
THE SECOND CALL
IS TO YOUR PAROLE OFFICER.

46:48.542 --> 46:50.083
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

47:05.166 --> 47:07.333
I NEED A SERGEANT.

47:13.333 --> 47:15.458
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

47:17.458 --> 47:19.000
MORGAN.

47:22.000 --> 47:23.709
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

47:23.709 --> 47:25.333
LaGuerta: ESTá LISTO.

47:25.333 --> 47:27.083
[ LAUGHS ]

47:27.083 --> 47:29.625
YA LO TIRé.

47:29.625 --> 47:32.667
OSCARSITO.

47:32.667 --> 47:34.125
iTíO ROBERTO!

47:35.625 --> 47:37.625
THE UNCLE CALLED OUR OFFICE
THIS MORNING.

47:37.625 --> 47:41.125
HE LIVES IN TAMPA.

47:41.125 --> 47:42.834
THAT'S GREAT.

47:42.834 --> 47:44.709
HE SHOULD BE WITH FAMILY.

47:44.709 --> 47:46.125
CAN I TAKE HIM HOME?

47:47.500 --> 47:48.959
WE'RE GOOD.

47:48.959 --> 47:50.959
MM-HMM.

47:50.959 --> 47:53.208
THANK YOU.

47:53.208 --> 47:54.959
THANK YOU FOR FINDING HIM,
HUH?

47:54.959 --> 47:56.959
HE'S A VERY SPECIAL BOY.

47:56.959 --> 47:59.166
I KNOW.

48:04.417 --> 48:06.333
CUíDATE, ¿HUH?

48:22.750 --> 48:24.667
L.T.,
YOU NEED TO SEE THIS.

48:35.250 --> 48:36.333
YOU OKAY?

48:36.333 --> 48:38.041
THESE CONTACTS.

48:42.458 --> 48:44.583
DIOS MíO.

48:48.917 --> 48:51.792
WRECKS LIKE THIS
ARE USUALLY SOLD FOR SCRAP.

48:51.792 --> 48:53.709
THE HUSBAND STASHES
A KNIFE INSIDE

48:53.709 --> 48:57.333
AND LETS A DEMO CREW SHRED
THE TRUCK BEFORE WE FIND IT.

48:57.333 --> 48:59.208
NO MORE MURDER WEAPON.

48:59.208 --> 49:00.583
THERE'S BLOOD.

49:00.583 --> 49:02.250
WANT TO BET
IT'S THE WIFE'S?

49:02.250 --> 49:04.875
IT'S ALWAYS THE HUSBAND.
YOU WERE RIGHT ALL ALONG.

49:04.875 --> 49:06.875
SHAKE IT OFF, MORGAN.
HOMICIDE TAKES TIME.

49:06.875 --> 49:09.375
Dexter:
DEB WILL FORGIVE ME EVENTUALLY.

49:09.375 --> 49:10.875
THAT'S WHO SHE IS --

49:10.875 --> 49:13.792
BIGHEARTED, KIND,
NOTHING LIKE ME.

49:13.792 --> 49:16.875
LaGUERTA THOUGHT
YOU SHOULD SEE THIS.

49:16.875 --> 49:20.208
THAT KID OSCAR
SWEARS THIS IS WHO HE SAW.

49:25.208 --> 49:27.458
SON OF A BITCH.

49:27.458 --> 49:28.709
DEX.

49:28.709 --> 49:30.959
OKAY, I GAVE THEM JORGE'S SOCK,

49:30.959 --> 49:34.291
A KNIFE WITH HIS PRINTS,
AND A DROP OF HIS WIFE'S BLOOD.

49:34.291 --> 49:36.000
FORENSICS TRIFECTA LIKE THAT

49:36.000 --> 49:38.291
SHOULD TRUMP
A CHILD'S DRAWING...

49:38.291 --> 49:39.750
I HOPE.

49:46.834 --> 49:48.583
[ LAUGHS ]

49:48.583 --> 49:50.583
TOO FUCKING WEIRD.

49:50.583 --> 49:52.250
JESUS CHRIST
SAVED THIS KID.

49:52.250 --> 49:55.083
ON HIS OWN
FOR AS LONG AS OSCAR WAS,

49:55.083 --> 49:56.250
WHO'S TO SAY HE DIDN'T?

50:04.959 --> 50:06.458
WHEN DID LIGHTING CANDLES

50:06.458 --> 50:08.542
BECOME MORE FUN
THAN BLOWING THEM OUT?

50:08.542 --> 50:11.792
NICE TURNOUT.

50:11.792 --> 50:14.000
I CALLED ALL THE MOMS
TO ASSURE THEM

50:14.000 --> 50:16.667
THAT PAUL WOULD NOT
BE MAKING AN APPEARANCE.

50:18.083 --> 50:19.542
DO ASTOR AND CODY KNOW

50:19.542 --> 50:21.291
THAT YOU TOLD THEIR DAD
NOT TO COME?

50:25.625 --> 50:27.041
AFTER PRESENTS.

50:29.959 --> 50:32.458
READY?

50:35.000 --> 50:36.792
MAKE A WISH, BABY.

50:36.792 --> 50:38.917
JUST DON'T TELL ANYBODY,
OR IT WON'T COME TRUE.

50:38.917 --> 50:41.792
IT ALREADY CAME TRUE.
DAD'S NOT HERE.

50:43.250 --> 50:46.208
[ LAUGHS ]

50:48.625 --> 50:50.333
I WANT THE MIDDLE PIECE.

50:50.333 --> 50:51.500
OKAY.

50:51.500 --> 50:54.500
I WAS WRONG ABOUT BIRTHDAYS.

50:54.500 --> 50:57.667
MAYBE THE REASON TO CELEBRATE
THEM IS WHAT THEY OFFER --

50:57.667 --> 51:00.333
THE HOPE OF LIVING
TO SEE ANOTHER ONE.

51:02.250 --> 51:04.875
THE THING ABOUT DEB
FORGIVING ME --

51:04.875 --> 51:09.583
I BETTER GIVE HER
A FEW MORE DAYS.

51:12.500 --> 51:15.792
I BARELY ESCAPED
GETTING CAUGHT THIS TIME.

51:15.792 --> 51:18.500
I REALIZE NOW
MY DAYS ARE NUMBERED.

51:20.000 --> 51:22.959
SO I BETTER MAKE
THE MOST OF THEM.

51:22.959 --> 51:26.333
[ LAUGHING ]

51:31.959 --> 51:34.750
ALL ALONG,
I THOUGHT THIS WAS A GAME

51:34.750 --> 51:38.375
MY ALTER EGO AND I
WERE PLAYING.

51:38.375 --> 51:40.917
BUT RELATIONSHIPS CHANGE,

51:40.917 --> 51:42.917
EVOLVE,

51:42.917 --> 51:44.250
AND THIS ONE'S GETTING DEEP.

51:44.250 --> 51:47.041
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

51:52.583 --> 51:55.125
LIKE HARRY SAID IN MY DREAM...

51:56.125 --> 51:58.542
...THE STORM'S ON ITS WAY.

